rom investors including Ant Group, Cathay Capital, and others\n\n### 2. **Cursor and Antigravity**\n- Mentioned in multiple results as examples of popular AI IDEs\n- These were referenced in context of voice input integrations that launched on Product Hunt during February 2025\n\n### 3. **Inspector**\n- Launch date: February 12, 2025\n- Description: Visual editing tool that connects with AI assistants like Claude Code, Codex, and Cursor\n- Feature: Click elements in UI to make visual adjustments, and it automatically writes changes to your codebase\n- Claimed to be \"the most complete AI builder\"\n\n### Other Notable Product Hunt Launches in February 2025:\n- **Code Arena**: Tool to compare multiple AI development applications side-by-side\n- **Supaboard AI**: AI business intelligence platform (daily and weekly champion on Feb 5)\n\n**The standout AI IDE launch from February 2025 appears to be Atoms by DeepWisdom**, which achieved remarkable commercial success with $1M+ ARR shortly after launch.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
