urce under Apache 2.0 license\n- Connects Google's Gemini 2.5 Pro model to local codebases\n- Supports natural language requests for code explanation, debugging, and new feature generation\n- Allows reading/writing files, executing shell commands, and interacting with tools\n- Supports Model Context Protocol (MCP) for agent interoperability\n\n### 3. **CloudBase AI CLI (by Tencent)**\nUpgraded from their previous CloudBase AI ToolKit on **August 15, 2025**, with continued updates into 2026:\n- First unified AI CLI management tool\n- One command to manage all mainstream AI tools (Claude Code, OpenAI Codex, aider, Qwen Code, etc.)\n- Supports custom models + built-in Chinese models (Hunyuan, DeepSeek, Kimi K2, GLM-4.5)\n- Automated workflow from coding to deployment (Web/mini-programs/backend services)\n\n### 4. **Qoder CLI (by Alibaba)**\nMentioned in the search results as a terminal-based AI programming tool that enables one-click AI programming directly from the command line.\n\n## 2026 AI CLI Trend Summary\n\nThe search results indicate that **early 2026 marked a significant shift** in AI developer tools, characterized by:\n- Movement from IDE-embedded \"chat completions\" to **CLI-based agentic execution**\n- Tools that can autonomously run commands, fix errors, and verify results\n- **Million-token context windows** for understanding entire project codebases\n- Tools becoming \"Swiss Army knives\" rather than just chat assistants\n\nThe articles specifically mention that **2026 is \"the explosive year for agentic AI tools, particularly Agentic CLI\"**, with February 2026 being a key period for adoption and maturation of these technologies.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
