ss, intelligent file management, 9+ format previews\n\n### 2. **GitHub Agentic Workflows (gh-aw)**\n- Featured in hot GitHub projects for early February 2026\n- Part of the AI coding agent orchestration trend\n\n### 3. **Maestro - Agent Orchestration Command Center**\n- TypeScript-based AI agent orchestration command center\n- Helps schedule and manage multiple AI agents for complex tasks\n\n### 4. **Kimi Code CLI**\n- Described as \"your next CLI agent\"\n- Part of a comprehensive agent toolkit\n\n### 5. **badlogic's Agent Toolkit**\n- All-in-one AI assistant toolkit\n- Includes coding agent CLI, unified LLM API, TUI & web UI libraries, Slack bot, vLLM pods\n\n## 📊 Key Trends in February 2026\n\nThe search results indicate several major trends in AI coding CLI agents:\n\n1. **Multi-Agent Orchestration**: Tools focusing on managing multiple AI agents working together\n2. **Cross-Platform Integration**: Desktop applications that provide GUIs for CLI tools\n3. **Unified Interfaces**: Platforms that integrate multiple LLM providers (OpenAI, Claude, Gemini, etc.)\n4. **GitHub Integration**: Agents that work directly with GitHub workflows and actions\n5. **Autonomous Development**: Agents capable of planning, coding, testing, and deploying with minimal human intervention\n\n## 🔧 Popular CLI Coding Agent Tools Mentioned\n\n- **Gemini CLI** (Google's open-source AI agent)\n- **GitHub Copilot CLI**\n- **Claude Code**\n- **Mentat**\n- **ShellGPT**\n- **Warp**\n\nThe trend shows a shift from single-model tools to comprehensive agent orchestration platforms with enhanced automation capabilities.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
